🎹 The 12 Keys (Canonical Scale)

Each key has:
	•	Name (system function)
	•	Music Interval Feel
	•	Abstraction
	•	Use Cases

⸻

1. Initiate (Root / Unison)

Function: Start, seed, create state
	•	Abstraction: S₀ exists
	•	Use:
	•	start project
	•	define variable
	•	introduce idea

👉 Without this, nothing exists.

⸻

2. Differentiate (Minor 2nd – tension)

Function: Create distinction / contrast
	•	Abstraction: A ≠ B
	•	Use:
	•	segmentation
	•	classification
	•	edge detection

👉 Creates information.

⸻

3. Relate (Major 2nd – movement)

Function: Connect elements
	•	Abstraction: A ↔ B
	•	Use:
	•	mapping ideas
	•	building networks
	•	analogies

👉 Enables structure.

⸻

4. Sequence (Minor 3rd – progression)

Function: Order in time
	•	Abstraction: A → B → C
	•	Use:
	•	workflows
	•	narratives
	•	algorithms

👉 Enables causality.

⸻

5. Stack (Major 3rd – structure)

Function: Build hierarchy
	•	Abstraction: levels / layers
	•	Use:
	•	org structures
	•	abstractions
	•	system architecture

👉 Enables scaling.

⸻

6. Convert (Perfect 4th – shift)

Function: Transform state
	•	Abstraction: A → B (rule)
	•	Use:
	•	money → asset
	•	data → insight
	•	input → output

👉 Enables utility.

⸻

7. Balance (Tritone – tension/resolution axis)

Function: Stabilize / counteract
	•	Abstraction: forces equalize
	•	Use:
	•	feedback control
	•	risk management
	•	negotiation

👉 Prevents collapse.

⸻

8. Amplify (Perfect 5th – power)

Function: Increase magnitude
	•	Abstraction: A × k
	•	Use:
	•	growth
	•	virality
	•	leverage

👉 Drives impact.

⸻

9. Resonate (Minor 6th – emotional alignment)

Function: Synchronize patterns
	•	Abstraction: phase alignment
	•	Use:
	•	branding
	•	social cohesion
	•	music / UX

👉 Drives adoption.

⸻

10. Cycle (Major 6th – return)

Function: Repeat / loop
	•	Abstraction: φ mod 2π
	•	Use:
	•	habits
	•	markets
	•	seasons
	•	oscillations

👉 Enables predictability.

